  "prompt": "What is a charter school?",
  "response": "A charter school is a publicly funded school that operates independently from the traditional public school system. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Publicly funded: Receives government funding based on student enrollment\n\n2. More autonomy: Has greater flexibility in curriculum, teaching methods, and school management compared to traditional public schools\n\n3. Open enrollment: Typically free and open to all students, often with admission by lottery if demand exceeds capacity\n\n4. Accountable to performance: Must meet specific academic and financial standards set by their charter to maintain authorization\n\n5. Independently operated: Run by independent organizations or groups, not directly by school districts\n\n6. Varied educational approaches: Can focus on specific teaching methods, subjects, or student populations\n\n7. No tuition: Free to attend, like traditional public schools\n\n8. Can be started by teachers, parents, community organizations, or other groups\n\nCharter schools aim to provide alternative educational options and innovative approaches within the public school system.",
